title: Teen Figure Skater Lee Hae-in Wins Back-to-Back Junior Grand Prix Titles
text:
Teen figure skater Lee Hae-in won her second consecutive title at the International Skating Union Junior Grand Prix in Croatia on Saturday.

The victory qualifies her for the Junior Grand Prix Final in December, where the top six skaters of the season will compete.

Lee, 14, won the gold medal with a total of 203.40 points -- 134.11 points in the free skate and 69.29 in the short program -- beating out two Russians, Daria Usacheva (197.19 points) and Anna Frolova (181.96).

It followed her win at an earlier event in Latvia on Sept. 7, where she finished with 197.63 points.

Lee became the first Korean figure skater to win two Junior Grand Prix events in a row since now retired superstar Kim Yu-na in 2005. She will be the third Korean woman to skate in the Junior Grand Prix Final, after Kim Yu-na and Kim Ye-lim, who advanced last year.
